value.0: Utapau is an arid sinkhole world in the Utapau system of the Tarabba Sector in the Outer Rim Territories. Utapau is the homeworld of the Pau'ans and the Utai, more commonly referred to collectively as Utapauns. These species live in the many giant sinkholes that dott the planet's scrub-covered surface.

Dagobah is an Outer Rim planet in the Dagobah system. A remote world of swamps and forests, it serves as a refuge for Jedi Grand Master Yoda during his exile, but otherwise had no notable intelligent life.

Svivren is the Svivreni homeworld, an Outer Rim Territories world not too far from the planet Andasala. Despite the harsh nature of the mountainous world and its severe seasonal variation, Svivren became an important trading port, and its population of more than eight billion include large colonies of Humans and Sullustans. The importance of trade was reflected in the planet's Festival of Great Trade.

The planet is directly represented in the Galactic Senate, and it remains completely neutral during the Galactic Civil War. Svivreni law forbid the presence of any personal weapons, and any violent acts results in immediate execution; its well-armed security forces (obviously exempt from the law) carru out these harsh codes efficiently.
Alzoc is the primary star of the Alzoc system.

Sluis Van is the primary planet in the Sluis Sector of the Outer Rim and the homeworld of the Sluissi race. It is the site of an extensive deep-space docking facility and shipyard, the largest and most impressive in the area. The leader of Sluis Van is called a khedive.

The Sluissi were long supporters of the Galactic Republic, and they were disgusted at the great injustices done during its final years. The planet was represented in the Galactic Senate by Bor Gracus and then Corlissi Ludar until 22 BBY, when Sluis Van seceded shortly before the Clone Wars. During the Clone Wars, Sluis Van was a Separatist stronghold. At the end of the Clone Wars, Sluis Van, as well as many other Confederate worlds were placed in sieges, but Sluis Van held off the Republic. However, civilians didn't fare well, as mass starvation broke out on the planet as a result of the Outer Rim Sieges.
Bpfassh is an arid double planet in the Sluis Sector orbited by a complicated system of moons, located near Praesitlyn and Sluis Van. It is the homeworld of the Bpfasshi.

Sullust is the primary planet of the Sullust system in Sullustan Space, located in the Outer Rim at the conjuncture of the Rimma Trade Route and the Silvestri Trace. It is the homeworld of the Sullustans.

The planet joined the Galactic Republic when Sullustan merchants connected their planet to Tapani Sector with the Rimma Trade Route 5,500 BBY.

The world is volatile with hundreds of active volcanoes, producing a noxious, toxic atmosphere and intense electrical storms. These conditions, combined with the planet's rich mineral deposits, cause the native Sullustan inhabitants to live in underground caves. The underground caves are humid and cool, with a diverse biosphere supported by underground lakes. The planet was once known for its podraces. During the New Sith Wars, the Brotherhood of Darkness captured the planet.

Haruun Kal (Above the Clouds in Basic, also known as Haruun Kul or Al'Har I) is the homeworld of the famed Jedi Master Mace Windu. Its capital is Pelek Baw. It is on the Gevarno Loop.

The only inhabited world in the Al'Har system, Haruun Kal appears to be an oceanic world from space. However, this "ocean" is in fact a sea of toxic gases brought to the surface by volcanic activity, and broken by mountains and plateaus. Only the landmasses that reach into the atmosphere could support life, and thus it is high in these mountains and plateaus where native life evolves.

Tibrin is the home world of the Ishi Tib. The planet is completely covered by small oceans, with many coral reefs and sandbars protruding to the surface. The ocean currents distribute warm water around the planet creating a temperate zone which covers the entire planet. Ishi Tib cities are built on the reefs and even built out of their material. Edible seaweed is grown and fish are bred for food in Tibrin's underwater corrals. Because of the Ishi Tib's reliance on the planet's natural resources, environmental efforts are a primary consideration on the planet. Technology is carefully tested before it is implemented into their society. In an effort to further this environmentalism, Ishi Tib use beasts to perform many tasks on the planet that would normally be performed by machines.

The planet was ruled by the murderous dictator Suribran Tu, who sided with the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars. After Count Dooku conquered the world in 21 BBY, he offered to work with the Confederacy of Independent Systems, but was instead executed by Dooku to gain the sympathy and support of the Ishi Tib - which he did. Sora Bulq then was made temporary Confederate governor of Tibrin. Even after Tibrin joined the Confederacy, it was represented in the Galactic Senate by Gume Saam. It was the site of the Battle of Tibrin.

Naboo is a planet that is the sectorial capital of the Chommell Sector near the Outer Rim territories. It is a largely unspoilt world with large plains and forests and oceans. It is mostly known as the homeworld of notable historical figures who played major roles in the downfall of the Old Republic and the rise of the Galactic Empire, namely Padm Amidala, Supreme Chancellor Palpatine and Jar Jar Binks.

Naboo is an enigma to astrophysicists. Its porous, plasma-rich interior and lack of a molten core has been a phenomenon not found on any other known planet in the galaxy. The surface of Naboo is covered by dense swamps, rolling grass plains, seas and verdant hills. The largest mountain chain, the Gallo Mountains, bisects the largest continent and divides the great grass plains of the north from the Lianorm Swamp in the south. South of the Lianorm Swamp is the Paonga Sea, where at the bottom lay the Gungan city of Otoh Gunga.

Vandelhelm is a planet in the Expansion Region known for its starshipwrights. Even though it is located along the Rimma Trade Route, it was not discovered by the Republic until 22,000 years after its founding, by the independent prospectors Vandel and Helm, looking for rich minerals and metals.

After Vandel and Helm settled the planet with their families, now named "Vandelhelm", and after making finds on its surface, they used the profits to form the first Guild of Metalsmiths.

Monsolar was a backwater planet in the Alzoc system, with the the Sujimis sector of the Outer Rim Territories. The planet was home to the Syrox species of parasitic worm, which laid its eggs in the planet's rivers, where they were consumed by other animals and grew within their new hosts. The sentient natives of the planet lived in several warring tribal communities, most of which either worshiped or feared the Syrox.

Alzoc III was the third world in the Alzoc system of the Outer Rim Territories. It was a frozen world, dominated by arctic tundra and frozen wastes. This limited the amount of wildlife on the surface. The sole sentient species native to the planet was the Talz. Tall bipeds covered in gray-white fur, they were notable for their four eyes, an adaptation to dazzling sunlight reflected off snow.

While the planet was sporadically visited during the reign of the Galactic Republic, its major introduction to galactic society was through Imperial scouts. Discovering a world rich with natural resources and an available work force, the Empire secretly enslaved the planet, conscripting the natives to work in large mines. The extracted ore was then shipped off to Imperial shipyards; the valuable Alzoc Pearl was also collected

Behpour was a small arid planet very close to the Naboo sun. It had a core of green acidic lava that often burned its way to the surface forming lakes and rivers of acid. The acid burning up created amazing rock formations.
